323
00:15:20,337 --> 00:15:23,255
♪ ♪

324
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:25,425
[Ben] I love you, too.

325
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:30,346
[breath trembling]

326
00:15:30,347 --> 00:15:31,931
[sniffles]

327
00:15:46,029 --> 00:15:47,822
What can I do?

328
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:51,241
Nothing.

329
00:15:51,242 --> 00:15:52,827
Thank you, though.

330
00:15:54,579 --> 00:15:56,456
Want to talk about it?

331
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:04,589
My-my dad had a heart attack
or a... a stroke.

332
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:08,842
He's in a coma now. No one knows
what's gonna happen.

333
00:16:08,843 --> 00:16:11,303
I'm so sorry.

334
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:14,348
I have to figure out
a-a plane ticket.

335
00:16:14,349 --> 00:16:15,724
I-I can do that.

336
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:17,893
You pack, and-and
I'll look for flights for you.

337
00:16:17,894 --> 00:16:19,687
Where's your computer?

338
00:16:19,688 --> 00:16:22,190
Never mind. I'll use my phone.

339
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:27,111
[chuckles] I don't even know
where you're from. Uh...

340
00:16:27,112 --> 00:16:30,072
What's the best airport
for you to fly into?

341
00:16:30,073 --> 00:16:32,157
You know what?
I can handle all of this.

342
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:33,742
Come on. You shouldn't
be alone right now.

343
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:35,160
Let me help you with this.

344
00:16:35,161 --> 00:16:36,870
No, I'm fine. Thank you.

345
00:16:36,871 --> 00:16:38,497
You don't have to be fine.

346
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:40,999
Something terrible
just happened. Let me help you.

347
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,419
